cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the integration of aerial mobile users into existing cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper presents an exact mathematical characterization of the coverage probability, which involves the analysis of signal propagation and interference, and hence can be related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the optimization of base station height and antenna down-tilt angle, which can have an impact on the quality of multimedia services provided by the cellular network. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the coexistence of terrestrial and aerial users in cellular networks, which can be viewed as a system control problem. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography and security, but the integration of aerial users into cellular networks can have implications for network security and privacy, and hence can be related to this sub-category.
